               <item n="m_translation_old">a1 The one to whom ones gives ... to eat or to drink, this one becomes under ones control. With that one 
a2 ... sesame,  mung bean, long pepper, cassia fistula, Dalbergia sissoo. As much as 
a3 everything is (available), as much indeed a single (person) pours it in ...-wise. One should mix together all these (ingredients). To whom      
a4 one gives that in the food or in the drink, this one becomes insane. If to return with the mind 
b1 one wishes, one should make a recitation (?) with milk containing sugar. It is good for him. Of the Daśamālā-sūtra
b2 this is the treatment. In front of the Buddha (statue) one should cast a spell on the Dalbergia sissoo 21. In whose name    
b3 they make [it], the (Dalbergia sissoo) has to be strewn over the earth that is expected to be walked on by him. [Then] they expel him from his own house. In case that
b4 one has the wish to pull out (a spike?) one should rise a hot pill from ... with the hand.   </item>
